    q: "My Bertazzoni gas range igniter won't spark — what's wrong?",
    a: "Three most common causes on Bertazzoni gas ranges, in diagnostic order: (1) Igniter electrode worn or fouled. The 2017-2021 Heritage series shows a consistent ignition system wear pattern around year 4-5, especially on units in LA coastal addresses (Santa Monica, Venice, Manhattan Beach, Pacific Palisades) where marine-layer humidity accelerates electrode oxidation. Surface burner ignition: replace the electrode for that zone, $165-$265. Oven ignition: replace the oven igniter, $145-$245. (2) Spark module failure (the electronic component that drives all the igniters from a single board). When one electrode is fully fouled and the others spark normally, electrode replacement is the fix. When all electrodes fail to spark, the module itself is suspect; $245-$385 replacement. (3) Gas valve or thermocouple issue (less common — usually accompanies a different symptom set like flame won't stay lit or pilot won't engage). On Heritage versus Professional and Master collection ranges, the igniter systems are slightly different: Heritage uses a different electrode geometry and a different module — we identify the collection during diagnostic so the right part ships. Diagnostic separates these in 15-20 minutes on-site."
