<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Bertazzoni is Italian — Guastalla, Emilia-Romagna, since 1882 — and we see it in LA kitchens where owners wanted European style without the Sub-Zero / Wolf price tag.</h2>

    <p>F.lli Bertazzoni S.p.A. has been making cooking equipment out of Guastalla in the Emilia-Romagna region since 1882, family-owned through five generations of the Bertazzoni family, and notably independent of the appliance conglomerates (BSH, Whirlpool, Electrolux) that consolidated most European cooking brands. In our 5-county SoCal service area, Bertazzoni cluster patterns are specific and identifiable: the Silver Lake, Los Feliz, and Echo Park renovation market where design-forward buyers chose Bertazzoni for the Italian aesthetic and the color-panel options; West Hollywood condos and townhomes where the 30-inch Master and Professional ranges fit the kitchen footprint and the price point sits comfortably between mass-market and luxury; Studio City, Sherman Oaks, and the Westside-adjacent neighborhoods where the Heritage collection (with its retro styling) anchors entirely new kitchen builds. Newport Beach, Costa Mesa, and parts of South Bay carry smaller but consistent installations.</p>

    <p>Two Bertazzoni-specific realities shape every service call we run. First, <strong>Bertazzoni's design language differentiates it from every other brand we service</strong>. The color-panel options (yellow, red, orange, white, black, stainless, and limited-run color releases) make a Bertazzoni range a kitchen design statement — and when a panel gets damaged during a renovation or fades from years of sun exposure on the range corner, panel replacement is a real service item that competitors don't even know exists. We coordinate panel orders through Bertazzoni USA distribution directly. Second, <strong>the three-collection split (Master / Professional / Heritage) means different parts ecosystems within the same brand</strong>. A Heritage 30-inch oven igniter is mechanically different from a Master 30-inch oven igniter — they look similar from outside but the part numbers don't cross. Diagnostic identifies which collection your unit belongs to first, which routes the correct parts on the first attempt. Service shops that don't know the collection split end up ordering the wrong parts and adding a second visit.</p>

    <p>This page covers Bertazzoni repair across the full US lineup — ranges (the bulk of the work), wall ovens, cooktops, dishwashers, refrigerator columns, range hoods. Every Bertazzoni service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Bertazzoni parts via Bertazzoni USA distribution, and an honest written quote with parts lead-time disclosed before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 RANGES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Bertazzoni range repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Master, Professional, Heritage — three collections, three service trees.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Ranges are the bulk of Bertazzoni's US lineup and the bulk of our Bertazzoni service work in LA. Three collections cover entry luxury (Master), mid-tier (Professional), and premium-retro (Heritage). All three are available in 30-inch, 36-inch, and 48-inch widths; gas and dual-fuel configurations dominant; induction less common. The service tree differs by collection.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>2017-2021 Heritage series igniter pattern (most common Bertazzoni service call in LA)</h3>
      <p>The Heritage 30-inch and 36-inch ranges produced between roughly 2017 and 2021 develop a consistent ignition system wear pattern around year 4 to 5 — accelerated in LA coastal addresses (Santa Monica, Venice, Manhattan Beach, Pacific Palisades) where marine-layer humidity oxidizes the electrode contacts faster than inland zones. Symptoms: oven igniter clicking but not lighting, surface burner zone clicking continuously without sparking, multi-burner units where one or two zones fail while others still work. Service path: identify the affected zones, replace the electrodes or oven igniter as needed (Heritage has a slightly different electrode geometry than Master and Professional collections — we confirm collection from the model tag on the back of the unit). <strong>Igniter $145-$245, electrode $165-$265 per zone — typically same-day when we stock the Heritage-specific parts.</strong> Coastal LA addresses we treat as accelerated-wear cohort and recommend a 4-year preventive inspection cadence.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the Heritage igniter pattern, Bertazzoni range service tree splits by component class. Most-common service items by year-window:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 3-5:</strong> Surface burner cap and ring wear (cosmetic / function), oven temperature sensor drift on convection units ($185-$285), igniter on Heritage cohort (above), and electrode wear across all collections.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-7:</strong> Oven thermostat ($245-$385), spark module failure on multi-zone failures ($245-$385), oven igniter on Master and Professional collections ($145-$245).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7-10:</strong> Convection fan motor — ThermalFlow dual-fan systems on Master and Professional ($325-$485). The dual-fan architecture distributes heat more evenly but doubles the fan-motor wear surface; replacement on heavily-used ovens is normal at this age.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-12:</strong> Oven door hinge assembly ($345-$525), oven door glass cracking from thermal cycling ($385-$680), gas valve replacement on the gas-line side ($445-$680).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10+:</strong> Control board ($385-$580), full door seal replacement, color-panel refresh on units where the original panel has faded from sun exposure (see panel-replacement FAQ above).</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The Heritage collection's retro styling adds a service consideration competitors miss: the brass knob and trim accents are specifically engineered to age gracefully (the Italian design intent is patina rather than replacement), but customers occasionally request replacement when the patina goes uneven or when a knob has been mishandled. We handle that as a coordination service through Bertazzoni USA. ThermalFlow versus Multiflow convection distinction matters during diagnostic: ThermalFlow uses two convection fans in a coordinated cycle, Multiflow uses a single high-output fan with directed airflow. Failure modes differ; we identify which system your range uses from the model tag before quoting fan-related work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 WALL OVENS, COOKTOPS, DISHWASHERS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Wall ovens, cooktops, dishwashers, refrigerator columns</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Beyond the freestanding ranges.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Bertazzoni's US lineup extends beyond ranges to cover wall ovens, cooktops, dishwashers, refrigerator columns, and range hoods. Lower volume in our service mix than the ranges, but real and recurring across the same Silver Lake / Los Feliz / West Hollywood demographic where Bertazzoni gets specified as a complete kitchen suite.</p>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Wall ovens (single and double, 30" / 36")</h3>
        <p>Electric wall ovens in single and double configurations. Service: bake/broil elements ($245-$385), oven temperature sensor ($185-$285), control board ($385-$580), convection fan motor ($325-$485). Master and Professional wall ovens share the same service tree; Heritage wall oven variants add the brass-trim and retro-styling considerations seen on the ranges.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Cooktops (gas, induction, dual-fuel)</h3>
        <p>Gas cooktops with sealed burner architecture, induction cooktops with full-surface zone detection, dual-fuel modular configurations. Service: burner igniter ($165-$265 per zone), induction zone generator board ($485-$780 per zone), surface burner cap and ring, gas valve assembly. Cooktop glass replacement on induction variants runs $580-$880.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Dishwashers (DW series)</h3>
        <p>Fully-integrated and panel-ready dishwashers. DW series shares engineering platform with select Italian dishwasher OEM suppliers (commonality at the component level with other Italian-built dishwashers). Service: drain pump ($285-$425), water inlet valve ($225-$345), control board ($385-$580), door latch and interlock.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Refrigerator columns (REF series)</h3>
        <p>24-inch and 36-inch refrigerator columns, single-zone and dual-zone variants. Service: water inlet valve ($185-$285), condenser fan motor ($285-$425), evaporator fan motor ($245-$385), door gasket replacement on units with custom panel installations. Refrigerator service tree shares patterns with the broader integrated-column refrigerator category.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Range hoods (matching collections)</h3>
        <p>Range hoods designed to match each Bertazzoni range collection visually — wall-mount, under-cabinet, and island configurations. Service: blower motor ($385-$580), fan switch, light socket and bulb. Color-panel options on hood matching the range panel for design coherence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Honest scope — what Bertazzoni doesn't make in US</h3>
        <p>No microwaves, washers, or dryers under the Bertazzoni brand in the US market. The brand's identity stays focused on cooking equipment + integrated kitchen support (dishwashers, refrigeration, ventilation). If you have a Bertazzoni-branded laundry appliance, it's almost certainly a European-market import — send us the model tag and we'll evaluate.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

