<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Bertazzoni jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Bertazzoni service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Bertazzoni HER304XFDXT Heritage 30" gas range, Silver Lake</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner noticed left-front surface burner clicking but not lighting. Oven igniter taking 30+ seconds to fire (normal is 8-15 seconds). Other burner zones still working normally. Unit was 5 years old, in the 2019 production cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2017-2021 Heritage series igniter wear pattern. Left-front electrode visually fouled with oxidation (Silver Lake address — humidity from the reservoir and the proximity to Echo Park Lake puts the home in our coastal-extension cohort). Oven igniter measured weak output but still functional. Spark module tested clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Left-front electrode replacement with OEM Bertazzoni Heritage-specific part (in stock on truck). Oven igniter replaced preventively at customer request. Verified spark and ignition on all four burner zones plus oven, multiple full cycles.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $375 total (paired electrode + igniter service). Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Bertazzoni MAST486GGASXE Master 48" dual-fuel range, Los Feliz</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner reported oven baking unevenly — front of pan browning normally, back staying pale across multiple bake cycles. Convection mode made the unevenness slightly worse, not better. Unit was 9 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> ThermalFlow dual-fan convection: rear fan motor running at reduced RPM (year 9 unit, bearing wear). Front fan motor measured within spec. Temperature sensor reading slightly off but within tolerance. Rear fan was the isolated failure; front fan within service life.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Rear convection fan motor replaced with OEM Bertazzoni part (in stock from Bertazzoni USA NJ on phone-identified symptoms, pre-ordered 5 days before visit). Verified even bake on test cycle in both convection and standard bake modes. Temperature sensor verified within tolerance — no replacement needed.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $445 total. Pre-ordered visit, 2 hours on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Bertazzoni HER304XFDXT Heritage 30" gas range, West Hollywood</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Color panel scratched during a kitchen cabinetry refresh (contractor's tool slipped against the front face of the range during cabinet pull). Owner wanted the panel replaced rather than living with the damage on a recent-renovation range.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Visual damage to the front panel, no mechanical issue with the range. Confirmed model and color code from the panel sticker (Heritage 30-inch in the matte black colorway). Ordered replacement panel through Bertazzoni USA distribution. 18-day lead time on this specific color/size combination — color panels aren't always stocked locally.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Returned 18 days later, replaced the front color panel with OEM Bertazzoni part. Re-aligned the panel mounting hardware. Cleaned and finished the surrounding area. Disposed of the original panel as recyclable steel per the owner's preference.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $675 total (panel + alignment labor). Two-visit timing with 18-day lead, 90 minutes on-site total.</p>
